      "date": "2025-12-22 23:33:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI attempted to fix the build errors present in this patch and succeeded. Yay! Now, keep in mind I barely have any idea what I am doing, so please doublecheck the changes I made to make sure they make sense.\n\nThis service is only provided in hopes to be useful and reduce latency from push to getting actual results in the face of trivial code errors\n\nHere's summary of my changes:\n## Fix Explanation\n\n**The Problem:**\nThe compile error occurred on line 11917 in `lustre/utils/lfs.c`. The error message indicated \"request for member 'has_arg' in something not a structure or union\", which is a typical C syntax error when struct member initialization is malformed.\n\n**The Root Cause:**\nA missing comma (`,`) after `\"write-lock\"` in the struct option initialization. The line read:\n```c\n{ .val = 'w',\t.name = \"write-lock\"\t.has_arg = no_argument },\n```\n\nWithout the comma between `.name = \"write-lock\"` and `.has_arg = no_argument`, the C compiler couldn't parse this as two separate member initializations and instead tried to interpret it as a single malformed expression.\n\n**The Fix:**\nAdded the missing comma after `\"write-lock\"`:\n```c\n{ .val = 'w',\t.name = \"write-lock\",\t.has_arg = no_argument },\n```\n\nThis is a simple typo that was introduced in the patch when adding long options to the `lfs_data_version` function. All other entries in the `long_opts` array have commas separating their member initializations, but this one was missing it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
